  "abstract": "Downy mildew or green car caused by\r\nSclerospora graminicola (Sacc.) Schroet. is\r\nthe mosl important disease of pearl millet\r\n[Pe1111isetum glaucum (L.) R. Br. emend.\r\nStuntz]. This causes severe loss in grain yield\r\ndue to complete or partial conversion of\r\nflorets into leafy structures (Singh et al. 1993).\r\nSince host-plant resistance is the most\r\nfeasible method to control this disease. about\r\n300 genetic stocks developed from the spontaneously\r\noccurring mutants in the world collection\r\nof pearl millet gcrmplasm were\r\nscreened for resistance to downy mi I dew. This\r\npaper contains the origin of the mutants and\r\ndevelopment of genetic stocks, describes\r\ntheir morphological and agronomical characters.\r\nand gives Lheir potential use in pearl\r\nmillet improvement...",
